During the course students get an overview of the nature and causes of death, injuries and their causing mechanisms, nature and causes of health damage, possibilities of laboratory investigations in solving juridical problems. Attention is paid to the importance of describing injuries and its role in determing mechanism and time of injuries and  to the juridical aspects of filling in medical documentation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give students basic knowledge of forensic medicine and understanding of solving medical-biological problems which rise up while proceeding criminal and civil cases. The aim is also to explain the role of medical doctor in solving juridical problems and give overview of their responsibilities in cases of death caused by external and natural causes and in examining injured patients.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students can examine and describe injuries, know mechanisms of their origin, know legislation of medico-legal investigation of deaths and living persons. Sudents know doctor's obligations for examining patients with health damages and dead bodies in cases of external causes of death and know expert's rights and obligations performing expertise. Students understand how significant it is to fill medical documentation correctly.
